title: Nonaqueous system secondary battery

events.title: Application filed by Japan Storage Battery Co Ltd

abstract:
PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED: To provide a nonaqueous system accumulator provided with superior safety, high energy density and a sufficient charge and discharge cycle characteristic.

SOLUTION: In the nonaqueous system accumulator 1, lithium nickel cobalt manganese composite oxide is used as active positive electrode substance, a thickness of a positive electrode 3 is ≥160 μm and ≤240 μm, and the mass of the lithium nickel cobalt manganese composite oxide coated on the positive collector is ≥38 mg/cm2and ≤65 mg/cm2per unit area of both sides of the positive collector.
